And this is coming from someone who does sell planners and journals.

Here‚Äôs the truth:
Digital products are so much bigger than aesthetics, Canva pages, and ‚Äúmanifest your goals‚Äù PDFs.

Planners and journals are great.
They‚Äôre an entry point.
They‚Äôre an add-on.
They work beautifully inside a bundle.

But they‚Äôre rarely the main revenue engine.

My highest money-makers are courses and ebooks.
Why? Because they solve real problems, create real transformation, and add value that lasts far longer than a few motivated days.

I also sell AI bots on a monthly recurring model, and yes- recurring revenue is powerful. Predictable. Scalable. Calm.
But even that works best when it‚Äôs built on deep value, not gimmicks.

And no, this isn‚Äôt about low-ticket vs high-ticket.

It‚Äôs about this:
üëâ Is your product worth the price you deserve to charge?
üëâ Does it actually improve someone‚Äôs life, not temporarily, but long-term?

The best digital products don‚Äôt just look good.
They change how people think, act, earn, or live.

Journals can support that journey.
They just shouldn‚Äôt be the whole journey.

That‚Äôs the difference between selling ‚Äúa product‚Äù
and building a real digital business.

EduPair is a tutoring platform built to help tutors spend more time teaching, and less time managing messages, schedules, homework, and payments.

We accept tutors worldwide, and prior tutoring experience is not required.
If you are a university student or recent graduate looking to earn income by teaching subjects you are confident in, EduPair is designed for you.

Tutors can teach online from anywhere, and those based in Hong Kong or the UK may also offer in-person lessons.

Signing up takes around five minutes, is completely free, and has no commitment.

EduPair is based in the UK and Hong Kong, and built for tutors globally.
